<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="78" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="78">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="78">This species, previously known only from Cuba, is now recorded from Haiti (new country and island record). Other specimens examined from Cuba, while similar in most other features, have the elytral base varying from all black to pale orange. Additional material is needed to fully understand the level of variation of this species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="78" type="new distributional data">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="78">New distributional data.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="78">Haiti, Ouest Department, Kenscoff, 1200 m, May 25, 1984, M. Thomas (1 specimen, FSCA).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
